    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-08-15T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-08-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="567"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d567">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">411.4931/8–1551: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Czechoslovakia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Briggs</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Praha</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-08-15">August 15,
                            1951</date>—noon.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>122. First official Czech reactions US economic retaliatory measures recd this
                    morning from Vilem Havelka, Centrotex official who in call at Consulate stated
                    fol: <list>
                        <label>(1)</label>
                        <item>Czech textile exports to US will be severely curtailed as result
                            announced withdrawal tariff concessions. Despite political situation, US
                            buyers have been anxious purchase Czech textiles, especially
                            jacquar-broadcloth, hat velours, etc. Loss of US market for Czech linen
                            goods would be particularly serious.</item>
                        <label>(2)</label>
                        <item>Centrotex concerned lest inability <gloss target="#t_Emb1">Emb</gloss>
                            certify invoices promptly might prevent Czech textiles from reaching US
                            in time for fall trade. In this connection he referred to
                            “inconvenience” to US importers.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Briggs</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
